quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":1.16,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"1.16\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.39,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.39\u00d7, interest cover 5.2\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":60.0,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 60% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":64.4,"pe_percentile":89.0,"median_pe":32.3,"earnings_yield_pct":1.55,"pb":8.92,"ev_ebitda":54.71,"quality_score":81.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":62.4,"peg":1.03,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 89-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 64.4\u00d7 earnings for ~62% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.03\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Mar 2023","Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[67.09,67.09,67.09,67.09,60.61,60.66,60.69,60.69,60.69,60.69,53.63,53.63],"latest_pct":53.63,"chg_1y_pp":-7.06},"FII":{"periods":["Mar 2023","Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[0.62,0.58,0.33,0.17,1.2,1.03,0.82,0.61,0.48,0.74,11.0,11.75],"latest_pct":11.75,"chg_1y_pp":11.14},"DII":{"periods":["Mar 2023","Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,2.18,2.85,2.24,1.92,0.15,0.15,0.46,1.71],"latest_pct":1.71,"chg_1y_pp":-0.21},"Public":{"periods":["Mar 2023","Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[32.29,32.33,32.58,32.73,36.01,35.46,36.26,36.78,38.67,38.41,34.92,32.91],"latest_pct":32.91,"chg_1y_pp":-3.87}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"22-Dec-2025","subject":"Face Value Split (Sub-Division) - From Rs 10/- Per Share To Rs 5/- Per Share","materiality":"High"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake down 7.06pp over ~1yr \u2192 53.63%.","FII":"FIIs adding (+11.14pp YoY \u2192 11.75%).","DII":"DIIs reducing (-0.21pp YoY \u2192 1.71%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"positive","score":4,"drivers":["+ Trades above its 200-day average (+40%).","+ 50-day average above the 200-day (golden cross).","+ Within 2% of its 52-week high.","+ Outpacing the NIFTY 500 by +168pp over 12 months."]